      <div class=3D"section section-anchor" id=3D"what-is-the-agile-manifes=
to" daa-lh=3D"s2"><div class=3D"content" daa-lh=3D"b1|content"><h2 id=3D"wh=
at-is-the-agile-manifesto">What is the Agile Manifesto?</h2></div>
       =20
        <div class=3D"section-metadata" data-block-status=3D"loaded">
          <div>
            <div>anchor</div>
            <div>what-is-the-agile-manifesto</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class=3D"section" daa-lh=3D"s3"><div class=3D"content" daa-lh=3D=
"b1|content"><p>The Agile Manifesto for Software Development is a declarati=
on that unifies the philosophy behind frameworks like <a href=3D"https://bu=
siness.adobe.com/blog/basics/what-is-scrum" daa-ll=3D"Scrum-1--">Scrum</a>,=
 Extreme Programming, and Feature-Driven Development (FDD). It represented =
a significant shift from the <a href=3D"https://business.adobe.com/blog/bas=
ics/waterfall" daa-ll=3D"waterfall style proj-2--">waterfall-style project =
management</a> approaches prevalent before its creation.</p><p>The <a href=
=3D"https://agilemanifesto.org/" daa-ll=3D"Manifesto for Agile -3--" target=
=3D"_blank">Manifesto for Agile Software Development</a> states:</p><p>=E2=
=80=9CWe are uncovering better ways of developing software by doing it and =
helping others do it.</p><p>Through this work, we have come to value:</p><u=
l>
          <li>Individuals and interactions over processes and tools</li>
          <li>Working software over comprehensive documentation</li>
          <li>Customer collaboration over contract negotiation</li>
          <li>Responding to change over following a plan</li>
        </ul><p>That is, while there is value in the items on the right, we=
 value the items on the left more.=E2=80=9D</p><p>Agile solutions emerge wh=
en self-organizing, cross-functional <a href=3D"https://business.adobe.com/=
blog/basics/agile-team" daa-ll=3D"Agile teams-4--">Agile teams</a> apply pr=
actices suited to their specific context. However, managers are still neede=
d to:</p><ul>
          <li>Create an environment conducive to team success.</li>
          <li>Ensure team members possess the necessary skill sets.</li>
          <li>Provide guidance when teams encounter unresolved issues.</li>
          <li>Remove obstacles and acquire external resources as needed.</l=
i>
        </ul></div>
